view.name: Women, Infants, Children (WIC) Vendor Information
view.attribution: New York State Department of Health
view.description:
The WIC Vendor Listing is compiled and published to provide WIC Participants with readily identifiable locations they can use to cash their WIC Benefits. The Special Supplemental Nutrition Program for Women, Infants and Children (WIC) offers nutrition education, breastfeeding support, referrals and a variety of nutritious foods to low-income pregnant, breastfeeding or postpartum women, infants and children up to age five to promote and support good health.
WIC improves the health of pregnant women, new mothers and their infants and children. The foods provided through WIC are a good source of nutrients often missing from the diets of women and young children. WIC participants have longer, healthier pregnancies and fewer premature births.

columns.name: Type
columns.description: Type of vendor; a grocery, a grocery with formula, a pharmacy, or a grocery with pharmacy.

columns.name: Facility Name
columns.description: Name of the vendor, with identifier if a chain.

columns.name: State
columns.description: State of vendor location, there are a few non-NYS vendors. NY – New York, OU – Out of NYS.

Disclaimers.Limitations: The list is in constant flux and can only be considered as accurate on the day of compilation.

Notes.Notes: The list is compiled from a list of WIC Approved New York State Vendors.  The vendors apply to participate in providing services to WIC participants. After a review of records, if approved, the vendor is listed as a WIC Approved Vendor which WIC Participants can use to cash their WIC Benefits.
